# Stellar Dominion — Leader System

## Four Leader Classes
| Class | Domain | Unique Role |
|---|---|---|
| `Commander` | Fleet combat, military operations | Admiral-equivalent |
| `Governor` | Planet management, population, economy | Colony administrator |
| `Scientist` | Research, exploration, anomaly resolution | Research director |
| `Strategist` | Strategic resources, megastructures, cascade prevention | **Original class — not in Stellaris** |

The Strategist is a deliberate addition. They are the only leader who can:
- Manage strategic resource logistics
- Oversee megastructure construction
- Apply cascade prevention bonuses (reduces cascade propagation speed)

## Trait Architecture
Four layers. A leader accumulates traits across their lifespan.

```
Background Traits (1, assigned at creation — 10 total pool)
    ↓
Level Traits (1 per level-up, player-chosen from pool of 3 — 20 total pool)
    ↓
Veteran Subclass Traits (1 at level 5, defines subclass — 3 per class = 12 total)
    ↓
Destiny Traits (1 at level 10, defines legacy — 4 total pool)
```

**Key departure from Stellaris:** Traits are **player-chosen at level-up** from a curated pool of 3 options — not randomized. This is intentional. Do not implement random trait assignment.

## LeaderData Resource
```gdscript
class_name LeaderData
extends Resource

@export_group("Identity")
@export var leader_name: String = ""
@export var leader_class: String = ""   # "commander" | "governor" | "scientist" | "strategist"
@export var portrait_id: String = ""

@export_group("Progression")
@export var current_level: int = 1
@export var experience: float = 0.0
@export var background_trait: String = ""
@export var level_traits: Array[String] = []
@export var veteran_trait: String = ""
@export var destiny_trait: String = ""

@export_group("Assignment")
@export var assigned_to: String = ""    # system_id, fleet_id, or "council"
@export var council_position: int = -1  # -1 = not on council
```

## Council System
7 positions. Unfilled positions apply penalties to their domain.

| Position | Domain | Unfilled Penalty |
|---|---|---|
| 0 | Military Affairs | -15% fleet combat power |
| 1 | Interior Affairs | -10% governor effectiveness |
| 2 | Science Directorate | -10% all research |
| 3 | Resource Oversight | -15% strategic resource income |
| 4 | Expansion Bureau | -20% colonization speed |
| 5 | Diplomatic Corps | -25% influence gain |
| 6 | Strategic Command | -20% megastructure build speed |

Penalties are applied as multipliers by `LeaderManager` during monthly tick.
Never hardcode penalty values — they must be `@export` on the council position data.

## 6 Council Agendas
Each agenda buffs its domain when active. Only one agenda active at a time.
Agendas are selected by the player from available options — not automatic.

## Legendary Paragon Leaders
5 Paragons seeded from existing planetary event chains. Each has unique unlock conditions.

| Paragon | Source Event | Unlock Condition |
|---|---|---|
| The Sleeping Leviathan | Biological modifier event | Befriend resolution path |
| The Godmachine | Precursor event | Peaceful integration path |
| Atmospheric Memory | Atmospheric modifier event | Full decoding complete |
| The Dry Docks | Precursor event | Ship restoration complete |
| The Buried Titan | Geological modifier event | Third resolution path |

Paragon leaders have one unique Paragon Trait not available to normal leaders.
They cannot be dismissed from the roster (only from council positions).

## LeaderManager Contract
```gdscript
LeaderManager.get_all_leaders()                          # → Array[LeaderData]
LeaderManager.get_council()                              # → Array[LeaderData] (7 slots, null = unfilled)
LeaderManager.assign_to_council(leader_id, position)     # → bool
LeaderManager.get_council_penalty(position: int)         # → float (multiplier, 1.0 = no penalty)
LeaderManager.level_up_leader(leader_id, chosen_trait)   # called after player picks trait
```
